decisions:
  - date: 2026-05-10
    decision: "MCP is now optional (Path A → B)"
    rationale: |
      User goal: maintain only rforge (not also rforge-mcp). Half of MCP's
      13 tools were placeholders; user is single-client (Claude Code, no
      Desktop/Cursor); plugin commands are markdown prompts that work via
      Claude Code's built-in tools without an MCP server.
    path_a_shipped:
      commit: <next>
      changes:
        - "package.json: drop peerDependencies.rforge-mcp"
        - "README.md: reframe Part 1 (MCP install) as optional"
        - "tests/test-plugin-structure.sh: remove Test 8 (peer-dep assertion)"
        - "CHANGELOG.md: document the decoupling in v1.2.0 entry"
    path_b_spec:
      file: docs/specs/SPEC-mcp-absorb-2026-05-10.md
      summary: |
        Migration plan for absorbing rforge-mcp's 7 implemented tools into
        rforge's lib/. 4 phases. Drops 6 placeholder MCP tools entirely.
        Estimated 3-4 sessions, not urgent — A already unblocks npm install.

